1
00:00:14,556 --> 00:00:15,975
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

2
00:00:29,446 --> 00:00:30,739
<i>SUBCOMMANDER?</i>

3
00:00:30,781 --> 00:00:32,491
YES?

4
00:00:32,533 --> 00:00:33,909
VULCAN:<i> DID I WAKE YOU?</i>

5
00:00:33,951 --> 00:00:35,786
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

6
00:00:35,828 --> 00:00:37,245
IS SOMETHING WRONG?

7
00:00:37,287 --> 00:00:39,498
<i>WE'VE LOCATED MENOS.</i>

8
00:00:40,916 --> 00:00:42,501
WHERE?

9
00:00:42,543 --> 00:00:45,128
VULCAN:<i> LESS THAN THREE DAYS</i>
<i>FROM YOUR PRESENT LOCATION.</i>

10
00:00:45,170 --> 00:00:47,464
ARE YOU CERTAIN IT'S HIM?

11
00:00:47,506 --> 00:00:49,466
<i>YES.</i>

12
00:00:54,262 --> 00:00:58,893
MAN: ♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

13
00:00:58,934 --> 00:01:02,062
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

14
00:01:02,103 --> 00:01:05,900
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

15
00:01:05,941 --> 00:01:09,611
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

16
00:01:09,653 --> 00:01:14,033
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

17
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:17,703
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

18
00:01:17,745 --> 00:01:21,707
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

19
00:01:21,749 --> 00:01:24,543
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

20
00:01:24,585 --> 00:01:27,922
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

21
00:01:27,963 --> 00:01:29,506
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

22
00:01:29,548 --> 00:01:33,092
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

23
00:01:33,134 --> 00:01:37,932
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

24
00:01:37,973 --> 00:01:40,350
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

25
00:01:40,392 --> 00:01:45,272
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

26
00:01:45,313 --> 00:01:47,983
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

27
00:01:48,025 --> 00:01:53,906
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

28
00:01:53,948 --> 00:01:55,657
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

29
00:01:55,699 --> 00:01:57,993
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

30
00:01:58,035 --> 00:02:01,914
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

31
00:02:01,956 --> 00:02:06,376
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

32
00:02:17,805 --> 00:02:19,014
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

33
00:02:19,056 --> 00:02:20,557
Archer: Come in.

34
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:24,561
GOOD MORNING.

35
00:02:24,603 --> 00:02:26,063
T'POL: CAPTAIN.

36
00:02:26,105 --> 00:02:27,022
TOAST?

37
00:02:27,064 --> 00:02:28,398
T'POL: NO, THANK YOU.

38
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:30,567
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

39
00:02:30,609 --> 00:02:32,444
ADMIRAL FORREST
WILL BE CALLING YOU

40
00:02:32,486 --> 00:02:33,904
THIS AFTERNOON, SIR.

41
00:02:33,946 --> 00:02:36,073
OH, REALLY?

42
00:02:36,115 --> 00:02:37,741
AND HOW WOULD YOU KNOW THAT?

43
00:02:37,783 --> 00:02:40,953
I WAS CONTACTED BY THE VULCAN
HIGH COMMAND LAST NIGHT.

44
00:02:40,995 --> 00:02:45,124
THEY'VE REQUESTED MY SERVICES
REGARDING A MATTER OF SECURITY.

45
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:49,294
AND THEY'VE ALREADY ASKED
ADMIRAL FORREST?

46
00:02:49,336 --> 00:02:51,755
HE SHOULD BE CONTACTING YOU
THIS AFTERNOON.

47
00:02:53,172 --> 00:02:54,925
A MATTER OF SECURITY?

48
00:02:54,967 --> 00:02:58,303
THE ADMIRAL WILL INFORM YOU
THAT<i> ENTERPRISE</i> WILL BE ASKED

49
00:02:58,345 --> 00:03:00,597
TO ALTER COURSE
TO THE PERNAIA SYSTEM,

50
00:03:00,639 --> 00:03:03,224
WHERE I WILL NEED A SHUTTLEPOD
AND A PILOT

51
00:03:03,266 --> 00:03:05,560
FOR THREE TO FIVE DAYS.

52
00:03:08,647 --> 00:03:12,484
YOU DIDN'T ANSWER MY QUESTION.

53
00:03:12,526 --> 00:03:15,029
WHAT KIND OF MATTER OF SECURITY?

54
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:17,156
A VULCAN SHIP WILL RENDEZVOUS
WITH THE SHUTTLEPOD

55
00:03:17,196 --> 00:03:19,158
WHEN MY MISSION IS COMPLETED.

56
00:03:22,452 --> 00:03:25,580
THEY'RE SENDING YOU
TO GET SOMEBODY --

57
00:03:25,622 --> 00:03:29,751
SOMEBODY YOU'LL BE HANDING OVER
TO THE VULCANS.

58
00:03:31,753 --> 00:03:33,547
WHY YOU?

59
00:03:35,132 --> 00:03:39,178
ADMIRAL FORREST WILL BE
CONTACTING YOU THIS AFTERNOON.

60
00:03:44,141 --> 00:03:47,268
THANKS FOR BEING
SO ENLIGHTENING.

61
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:48,770
DISMISSED.

62
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:05,120
ARCHER: CAPTAIN'S LOG,
SUPPLEMENTAL.

63
00:04:05,162 --> 00:04:08,540
AS ANTICIPATED, I WAS CONTACTED
BY ADMIRAL FORREST,

64
00:04:08,582 --> 00:04:10,542
WHO HAS ORDERED US
TO ACCOMMODATE

65
00:04:10,584 --> 00:04:12,169
THE VULCANS' REQUEST.

66
00:04:12,211 --> 00:04:13,921
ARCHER: DID YOU FIND
THE COORDINATES?

67
00:04:13,962 --> 00:04:15,172
TRIP: PERNAIA PRIME.

68
00:04:15,214 --> 00:04:16,924
YES, SIR.

69
00:04:16,965 --> 00:04:18,425
ARCHER: SET A COURSE.

70
00:04:18,466 --> 00:04:22,137
WHEN WE ARRIVE, YOU'LL BE
PILOTING THE SHUTTLEPOD.

71
00:04:22,179 --> 00:04:24,139
TRAVIS: WHERE EXACTLY
WILL WE BE GOING?

72
00:04:24,181 --> 00:04:26,808
ARCHER: SOMEWHERE IN
THE PERNAIA SYSTEM, NO DOUBT.

73
00:04:26,850 --> 00:04:29,061
AS FAR AS THE EXACT LOCATION,

74
00:04:29,103 --> 00:04:32,355
ADMIRAL FORREST
DOESN'T EVEN KNOW THAT.

75
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:35,525
SEEMS THE SUBCOMMANDER'S
ON A HIGHLY CLASSIFIED MISSION.

76
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:37,986
TRIP: IS THIS PERNAIA
PRIME INHABITED?

77
00:04:38,028 --> 00:04:41,031
THE VULCAN DATABASE SAYS IT HAS
A METHANE-BASED ATMOSPHERE.

78
00:04:41,073 --> 00:04:44,159
SO SHE'S GOING TO ANOTHER
PLANET IN THE SYSTEM.

79
00:04:44,201 --> 00:04:45,827
[ LAUGHS ]

80
00:04:45,869 --> 00:04:48,455
ARE WE SUPPOSED TO PLAY
SOME KIND OF GUESSING GAME?

81
00:04:50,124 --> 00:04:53,668
ARCHER: NO, WE'RE SUPPOSED
TO WAIT AT PERNAIA PRIME

82
00:04:53,710 --> 00:04:56,546
FOR T'POL AND TRAVIS
TO FINISH THEIR MISSION.

83
00:04:56,588 --> 00:04:59,174
AND DO WHAT
IN THE MEANTIME?

84
00:04:59,216 --> 00:05:02,094
REED: I COULD USE A FEW
DAYS TO RECALIBRATE
THE TORPEDO LAUNCHERS.

85
00:05:02,136 --> 00:05:06,098
I COULD POLISH ALL THE HANDLES
AND RAILS IN ENGINEERING.

86
00:05:08,683 --> 00:05:12,813
I GUESS I COULD PURGE
THE IMPULSE REACTORS.

87
00:05:12,854 --> 00:05:14,689
IT'S ONLY FOR A FEW DAYS.

88
00:05:14,731 --> 00:05:17,651
WE'VE GOT PLENTY
TO KEEP OURSELVES BUSY.

89
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:22,239
IS THERE ANYTHING SPECIFIC YOU
AND TRAVIS ARE GOING TO NEED?

90
00:05:23,991 --> 00:05:28,162
COLD-WEATHER GEAR,
RESTRAINTS, AND PHASE PISTOLS.

91
00:05:30,205 --> 00:05:33,458
[<i> CROWD CHEERING</i> ]

92
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:35,836
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

93
00:05:35,877 --> 00:05:37,004
COME IN.

94
00:05:41,175 --> 00:05:43,177
IF THE VULCAN HIGH COMMAND
DOESN'T APPROVE

95
00:05:43,218 --> 00:05:45,220
OF THE WATER-POLO MATCH
I'M WATCHING,

96
00:05:45,262 --> 00:05:47,597
I'D BE HAPPY TO FIND ANOTHER.

97
00:05:47,639 --> 00:05:51,185
T'POL: YOUR ORDERS TO BRING ME
TO PERNAIA CAME FROM STARFLEET,

98
00:05:51,226 --> 00:05:54,271
NOT THE HIGH COMMAND.

99
00:05:54,313 --> 00:05:56,231
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

100
00:05:56,273 --> 00:05:59,860
I HAVE A PERSONAL MATTER
I'D LIKE TO DISCUSS.

101
00:06:11,621 --> 00:06:13,790
[<i> CHEERING STOPS</i> ]

102
00:06:13,832 --> 00:06:16,168
T'POL: BEFORE I JOINED
THE SCIENCE DIRECTORATE,

103
00:06:16,210 --> 00:06:18,879
I WAS ASSIGNED
TO THE MINISTRY OF SECURITY.

104
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:22,841
I WAS TRAINED IN RECONNAISSANCE
AND RETRIEVAL.

105
00:06:22,883 --> 00:06:25,260
MOVE OVER, PORTHOS.
LET THE LADY SIT DOWN.

106
00:06:25,302 --> 00:06:28,555
SOUNDS LIKE THIS
IS GONNA BE GOOD.

107
00:06:28,596 --> 00:06:31,308
COME ON, SIT DOWN.

108
00:06:35,812 --> 00:06:37,898
HOW LONG AGO ARE
WE TALKING ABOUT?

109
00:06:37,939 --> 00:06:40,859
I COMPLETED MY TRAINING
17 YEARS AGO.

110
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:43,237
GO AHEAD.

111
00:06:43,278 --> 00:06:46,823
ARE YOU FAMILIAR
WITH A PLANET CALLED AGARON?

112
00:06:46,865 --> 00:06:49,826
THEY'RE CLOSE ALLIES
WITH THE VULCANS, RIGHT?

113
00:06:49,868 --> 00:06:51,703
NOT ALWAYS.

114
00:06:51,745 --> 00:06:55,123
AGARON WAS
A VERY CORRUPT WORLD.

115
00:06:55,165 --> 00:06:56,624
WHEN THEIR LEADERS
WERE FIRST TRYING

116
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:58,043
TO FORGE AN ALLIANCE
WITH VULCAN,

117
00:06:58,085 --> 00:06:59,961
THEY ASKED FOR OUR ASSISTANCE.

118
00:07:00,003 --> 00:07:01,838
THAT WAS NEARLY 30 YEARS AGO.

119
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:03,631
HUNDREDS OF OUR AGENTS

120
00:07:03,673 --> 00:07:05,842
WERE SURGICALLY ALTERED
AND SENT TO INFILTRATE

121
00:07:05,884 --> 00:07:08,636
THE MOST CRIMINAL FACTIONS
OF AGARON SOCIETY.

122
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:12,015
EVENTUALLY, THEY WERE
INSTRUMENTAL IN THE OVERTHROW

123
00:07:12,057 --> 00:07:13,558
OF THOSE FACTIONS.

124
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:18,605
YOU'RE NOT GONNA TELL ME
YOU'RE ONE OF THOSE AGENTS.

125
00:07:18,646 --> 00:07:20,440
I'M NOT<i> THAT</i> OLD, CAPTAIN.

126
00:07:20,481 --> 00:07:22,859
AFTER THE ALLIANCE
WAS FORMALIZED,

127
00:07:22,901 --> 00:07:25,779
THE VULCAN AGENTS WERE RECALLED.

128
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:29,657
THEY ALL RETURNED VOLUNTARILY --
ALL BUT 19.

129
00:07:29,699 --> 00:07:34,246
I GUESS EVEN VULCANS
CAN FALL PREY TO TEMPTATION.

130
00:07:34,288 --> 00:07:36,664
THE MINISTRY OF SECURITY
SENT A TEAM

131
00:07:36,706 --> 00:07:39,793
OF NEWLY TRAINED OPERATIVES
TO RETRIEVE THEM.

132
00:07:39,834 --> 00:07:41,962
I WAS ONLY ABLE
TO APPREHEND FIVE

133
00:07:42,003 --> 00:07:44,423
OF THE SIX FUGITIVES
ASSIGNED TO ME.

134
00:07:44,464 --> 00:07:49,094
SO, TOMORROW,
YOU GET TO PICK UP NUMBER SIX.

135
00:07:49,136 --> 00:07:52,639
WHY COULDN'T SOMEONE ELSE DO IT?
WHY YOU?

136
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:56,143
THE MINISTRY CONSIDERS IT
A MATTER OF HONOR.

137
00:07:56,184 --> 00:07:58,979
HOW VERY VULCAN.

138
00:07:59,020 --> 00:08:03,691
SO...WHY HAVE YOU DECIDED
TO TELL ME ALL THIS?

139
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:05,735
I'D LIKE YOU TO COME WITH ME.

140
00:08:05,777 --> 00:08:07,028
WHAT?

141
00:08:07,070 --> 00:08:08,363
THE MAN I'M BEING SENT
TO APPREHEND

142
00:08:08,405 --> 00:08:10,073
IS EXTREMELY DANGEROUS.

143
00:08:10,115 --> 00:08:12,200
IT WOULD BE WISE FOR ME
TO HAVE ASSISTANCE.

144
00:08:12,242 --> 00:08:15,536
YOU SAID
THERE'S A VULCAN SHIP COMING.

145
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:19,207
I'M SURE THEY CAN PROVIDE
ALL THE ASSISTANCE YOU'LL NEED.

146
00:08:19,249 --> 00:08:21,751
I'D PREFER IT
IF YOU'D COME WITH ME, CAPTAIN.

147
00:08:21,793 --> 00:08:23,586
WHY?

148
00:08:25,088 --> 00:08:27,966
I NEED TO BE
WITH SOMEONE I CAN TRUST.

149
00:08:29,301 --> 00:08:34,181
IF YOU DON'T WISH TO HELP ME,
I UNDERSTAND.

150
00:08:41,813 --> 00:08:43,148
GOOD NIGHT.

151
00:08:44,941 --> 00:08:47,777
WHAT'S HIS NAME?

152
00:08:47,819 --> 00:08:50,780
THE MAN WE'RE GOING
TO APPREHEND?

153
00:08:50,822 --> 00:08:53,408
MENOS.

154
00:08:55,827 --> 00:08:57,620
SEE YOU IN THE MORNING.

155
00:09:05,295 --> 00:09:06,713
TRIP: IF YOU AGREED
TO GO WITH HER,

156
00:09:06,754 --> 00:09:08,507
YOU MUST KNOW SOMETHING
ABOUT WHAT SHE'S UP TO.

157
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:10,384
WE'LL BE BACK
IN THREE TO FIVE DAYS, TRIP.

158
00:09:10,425 --> 00:09:12,552
IF THAT VULCAN SHIP
COMES SNOOPING AROUND,

159
00:09:12,593 --> 00:09:15,638
THE LAST THING YOU WANT TO TELL
THEM IS THAT I'M WITH T'POL.

160
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:17,098
TRIP: WHY'S THAT?

161
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:21,144
WHY WOULD YOU BEING WITH HER
BE A PROBLEM TO THEM?

162
00:09:21,186 --> 00:09:22,437
THREE TO FIVE DAYS, TRIP.

163
00:09:22,479 --> 00:09:23,855
COME ON, CAPTAIN.

164
00:09:23,897 --> 00:09:25,773
LAST NIGHT, YOU WERE
JUST AS FRUSTRATED AS I WAS

165
00:09:25,815 --> 00:09:27,442
ABOUT HAVING TO SIT
ON YOUR HANDS

166
00:09:27,484 --> 00:09:28,609
WHILE SHE GOES OFF AND DOES...

167
00:09:28,651 --> 00:09:31,029
WHATEVER IT IS
SHE'S GOING OFF TO DO.

168
00:09:34,657 --> 00:09:37,369
THIS ISN'T
JUST A CASE OF CURIOSITY.

169
00:09:37,411 --> 00:09:39,871
BUT WHAT IF YOU GET HURT,
KIDNAPPED?

170
00:09:39,913 --> 00:09:41,498
YOU PUT ME IN CHARGE
OF THIS SHIP.

171
00:09:41,540 --> 00:09:42,999
YOU WON'T TELL ME
WHERE YOU'RE GOING?

172
00:09:43,041 --> 00:09:45,001
HOW AM I SUPPOSED TO BE
A GOOD TEMPORARY CAPTAIN

173
00:09:45,043 --> 00:09:46,461
IF I DON'T KNOW
WHERE MY PEOPLE ARE?

174
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:48,255
TELL ME THAT.

175
00:09:48,296 --> 00:09:50,549
ARCHER: SHE'S GOT SOME
UNFINISHED BUSINESS, TRIP.

176
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:53,051
I'M NOT SURE WHY,
BUT SHE NEEDS ME TO GO ALONG.

177
00:09:53,093 --> 00:09:54,761
WE'LL BE OKAY.

178
00:09:54,802 --> 00:09:57,805
TRIP: THERE ARE
A LOT OF DEFINITIONS
OF UNFINISHED BUSINESS.

179
00:09:57,847 --> 00:09:59,933
COULD YOU BE
A LITTLE MORE SPECIFIC?

180
00:09:59,974 --> 00:10:01,226
ARCHER: YOU'RE
IN CHARGE, COMMANDER.

181
00:10:01,268 --> 00:10:03,353
HAVE YOU GIVEN TRAVIS
THE COORDINATES?

182
00:10:03,395 --> 00:10:04,729
T'POL: YES.

183
00:10:06,523 --> 00:10:08,567
HAVE FUN.

184
00:10:16,450 --> 00:10:18,326
T'POL: BEFORE HE WAS
SENT TO AGARON,

185
00:10:18,368 --> 00:10:20,828
THE DORSAL LOBES OF HIS EARS
WERE SURGICALLY ALTERED.

186
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:23,998
THE RIDGE ON HIS FOREHEAD
WAS ADDED SOMETIME AFTERWARD.

187
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:26,585
WHY DIDN'T HE WANT
TO COME HOME?

188
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:30,088
HE WAS ASSIGNED TO INFILTRATE
A CELL OF SMUGGLERS.

189
00:10:30,130 --> 00:10:31,756
HE LEARNED THEIR CRAFT.

190
00:10:31,798 --> 00:10:35,885
HE BECAME VERY PROFICIENT AT IT,
AMASSED A LARGE FORTUNE.

191
00:10:35,927 --> 00:10:37,387
SMUGGLING WHAT?

192
00:10:37,429 --> 00:10:38,763
SYNTHETIC BIO-TOXINS

193
00:10:38,805 --> 00:10:42,476
USED TO MANUFACTURE
TRANSGENIC WEAPONS.

194
00:10:44,603 --> 00:10:47,272
I SPENT THREE MONTHS
TRYING TO FIND HIM.

195
00:10:47,314 --> 00:10:49,149
HE USED HIS WEALTH WISELY.

196
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:50,650
WHENEVER I'D GET CLOSE,

197
00:10:50,691 --> 00:10:53,403
I'D FIND HE'D LEFT
A DAY OR TWO BEFORE.

198
00:10:53,445 --> 00:10:54,946
YOU NEVER FOUND HIM?

199
00:10:54,988 --> 00:10:57,991
ONLY ONCE, ON RISA.

200
00:10:59,284 --> 00:11:02,370
THEY THOUGHT
THEY WERE INVULNERABLE.

201
00:11:02,412 --> 00:11:03,746
THEY?

202
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:05,624
HE.

203
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:07,834
HE THOUGHT HE WAS
INVULNERABLE THERE,

204
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:10,462
THAT NO ONE WOULD
THINK TO LOOK FOR HIM

205
00:11:10,504 --> 00:11:12,046
ON SUCH A PEACEFUL PLACE.

206
00:11:12,088 --> 00:11:14,007
WHAT HAPPENED?

207
00:11:17,135 --> 00:11:19,929
I GOT VERY CLOSE --

208
00:11:19,971 --> 00:11:23,933
20 METERS...MAYBE 10.

209
00:11:23,975 --> 00:11:25,935
[ PANTING ]

210
00:11:25,977 --> 00:11:28,021
T'POL?

211
00:11:30,023 --> 00:11:32,359
I NEVER FOUND HIM AGAIN.

212
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:36,695
NO ONE DID...NOT UNTIL NOW.

213
00:11:44,371 --> 00:11:46,665
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

214
00:12:06,017 --> 00:12:08,186
[ SCANNER BEEPING ]

215
00:12:08,228 --> 00:12:09,854
HE'S HERE.

216
00:12:18,154 --> 00:12:20,198
WHERE?

217
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:24,244
WITHIN 30 METERS.

218
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:27,497
IF HE SEES T'POL, HE MAY
TRY TO GET TO HIS SHIP.

219
00:12:41,678 --> 00:12:43,722
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

220
00:13:00,113 --> 00:13:02,115
[ COINS CLATTERING ]

221
00:13:36,691 --> 00:13:38,192
T'POL: HE SAW ME.

222
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:40,320
ARCHER: WHICH WAY?
T'POL: I'M NOT CERTAIN.

223
00:13:43,114 --> 00:13:44,407
[ WHISTLES ]

224
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:48,035
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

225
00:13:57,754 --> 00:13:58,921
[ GRUNTS ]

226
00:13:58,963 --> 00:14:01,299
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

227
00:14:01,341 --> 00:14:03,426
COULDN'T AGREE MORE.

228
00:14:07,096 --> 00:14:08,889
DON'T MOVE.

229
00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:22,987
YOU HAVE NO JURISDICTION HERE.

230
00:14:24,781 --> 00:14:26,700
FOLLOW ME.

231
00:14:32,497 --> 00:14:33,790
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

232
00:14:33,832 --> 00:14:35,124
TRIP: COME IN.

233
00:14:35,166 --> 00:14:36,417
GENTLEMEN, COME IN.

234
00:14:36,459 --> 00:14:38,378
GLAD YOU COULD JOIN ME.

235
00:14:38,419 --> 00:14:39,838
REED: WATER POLO?

236
00:14:39,879 --> 00:14:42,256
VERY EXCITING SPORT.
YOU SHOULD LEARN MORE ABOUT IT.

237
00:14:42,298 --> 00:14:44,925
PLEASE SIT DOWN.

238
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:49,222
I HAD CHEF PREPARE
A SPECIAL LUNCH --

239
00:14:49,263 --> 00:14:51,307
BANGERS AND MASH FOR YOU

240
00:14:51,349 --> 00:14:52,767
AND, UH, DENOBULAN SAUSAGE
FOR THE DOCTOR.

241
00:14:52,809 --> 00:14:54,310
PHLOX: VERY NICE.

242
00:14:54,352 --> 00:14:56,270
REED: ARE YOU SURE THE CAPTAIN
WOULDN'T HAVE A PROBLEM

243
00:14:56,312 --> 00:14:57,731
WITH YOU USING HIS DINING ROOM?

244
00:14:57,772 --> 00:14:59,733
WELL, ACTING CAPTAIN,
CAPTAIN'S MESS --

245
00:14:59,774 --> 00:15:02,360
I DON'T SEE A PROBLEM.

246
00:15:02,402 --> 00:15:04,445
THANK YOU, CREWMAN.

247
00:15:08,949 --> 00:15:10,159
ENJOY.

248
00:15:10,201 --> 00:15:13,120
PHLOX: THANK YOU.

249
00:15:13,162 --> 00:15:16,791
OH, I DETECTED A LYMPHATIC VIRUS
ONBOARD THIS MORNING.

250
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:18,167
MOST LIKELY IT SNEAKED IN

251
00:15:18,209 --> 00:15:20,545
WITH ONE OF THE, UH,
DEUTERIUM CANISTERS.

252
00:15:20,587 --> 00:15:22,797
WE SHOULD PROBABLY
INOCULATE THE CREW.

253
00:15:22,839 --> 00:15:25,049
WHY DIDN'T THE BIO-SCANNERS
DETECT IT?

254
00:15:25,091 --> 00:15:28,135
WELL, IT'S A VERY RELIABLE
DEVICE, BUT IT'S NOT PERFECT.

255
00:15:28,177 --> 00:15:30,805
THE INOCULATION DOES HAVE
SOME, UM, SIDE EFFECTS.

256
00:15:30,847 --> 00:15:32,473
WHAT KIND OF SIDE EFFECTS?

257
00:15:32,515 --> 00:15:35,351
MM, HEADACHE, NAUSEA, DIARRHEA.

258
00:15:35,393 --> 00:15:37,604
BUT THEY WOULD SUBSIDE
IN A DAY OR TWO.

259
00:15:37,645 --> 00:15:41,274
DO I HAVE YOUR, UH, PERMISSION?

260
00:15:41,315 --> 00:15:43,317
I'D HATE TO BE RESPONSIBLE

261
00:15:43,359 --> 00:15:45,986
FOR GIVING THE CREW
THE -- THE RUNS.

262
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:48,989
MAYBE YOU SHOULD WAIT
TILL THE CAPTAIN GETS BACK.

263
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:51,242
I'M AFRAID THE VIRUS
WILL HAVE SPREAD BY THEN.

264
00:15:51,284 --> 00:15:53,828
I REALLY NEED AN ANSWER TODAY.

265
00:15:53,870 --> 00:15:55,288
[ SIGHS ]

266
00:15:55,329 --> 00:15:57,248
WHY DON'T I GET
BACK TO YOU LATER, DOC?

267
00:15:57,290 --> 00:16:00,126
NOT, UH, TOO MUCH LATER, HMM?

268
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:03,170
REED: WHILE WE'RE ON THE
SUBJECT OF APPROVALS,

269
00:16:03,212 --> 00:16:04,631
I PROMISED CAPTAIN ARCHER

270
00:16:04,672 --> 00:16:07,007
THAT I'D RECALIBRATE
THE TORPEDO LAUNCHERS.

271
00:16:07,049 --> 00:16:10,136
I'LL NEED TO DIVERT COMPUTER
ACCESS FROM MAIN ENGINEERING.

272
00:16:10,177 --> 00:16:12,388
THAT WOULD MEAN WE'D HAVE
TO POWER DOWN THE WARP CORE.

273
00:16:12,430 --> 00:16:15,850
IT'LL ONLY BE FOR A DAY. WE'RE
NOT EXACTLY GOING ANYWHERE.

274
00:16:15,892 --> 00:16:17,852
WELL, WE'RE ALSO NOT AT WAR.

275
00:16:17,894 --> 00:16:20,688
I'M JUST NOT COMFORTABLE TAKING
THE ENGINES OFFLINE RIGHT NOW.

276
00:16:20,730 --> 00:16:25,985
IS THAT THE CHIEF ENGINEER
TALKING OR THE ACTING CAPTAIN?

277
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:28,362
[ SIGHS ]

278
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:30,197
LET ME GET BACK TO YOU.

279
00:16:31,449 --> 00:16:34,619
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

280
00:16:34,661 --> 00:16:36,203
TUCKER.

281
00:16:36,245 --> 00:16:38,998
Hoshi: We were just hailed
by the Vulcan ship<i> Nyran,</i> sir.

282
00:16:39,039 --> 00:16:40,917
It's approaching the system
at high warp.

283
00:16:40,959 --> 00:16:44,504
They're asking to speak
with Captain Archer.

284
00:16:44,545 --> 00:16:46,923
TELL THEM, UM...

285
00:16:46,965 --> 00:16:49,175
THE CAPTAIN'S INDISPOSED
AT THE MOMENT.

286
00:16:49,216 --> 00:16:51,344
HE'LL GET BACK TO THEM
IN A LITTLE WHILE.

287
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:54,180
Hoshi: Yes, sir.

288
00:16:54,221 --> 00:16:57,433
THE CAPTAIN SAID NOT TO TELL
THE VULCANS HE WENT WITH T'POL.

289
00:16:57,475 --> 00:16:59,853
HE WAS, UM -- HE WAS
VERY EMPHATIC ABOUT THAT.

290
00:16:59,894 --> 00:17:01,646
PHLOX: IT'S GOING
TO BE DIFFICULT

291
00:17:01,688 --> 00:17:03,439
TO CONVINCE THEM
HE'S, UH, INDISPOSED

292
00:17:03,481 --> 00:17:05,024
FOR THE NEXT FOUR DAYS.

293
00:17:07,318 --> 00:17:10,530
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

294
00:17:10,571 --> 00:17:12,323
GO AHEAD.

295
00:17:12,365 --> 00:17:15,075
HOSHI: Captain Tavek says he has
a message from Admiral Forrest.

296
00:17:15,117 --> 00:17:17,745
He seems very anxious
to speak with Captain Archer.

297
00:17:17,787 --> 00:17:20,498
What shall I tell him?

298
00:17:20,540 --> 00:17:22,917
I'LL GET BACK TO YOU.

299
00:17:28,631 --> 00:17:30,550
[ SIGHS ]

300
00:17:33,344 --> 00:17:34,554
YOUR WARRANT IS VALID,

301
00:17:34,595 --> 00:17:37,306
BUT YOU WON'T BE ABLE
TO TAKE HIM --

302
00:17:37,348 --> 00:17:39,684
NOT FOR AT LEAST FOUR HOURS.

303
00:17:39,726 --> 00:17:42,186
WE'VE BEGUN THERMALIZING
THE LANDING DECK.

304
00:17:42,228 --> 00:17:44,313
WE JUST NEED TO GET HIM
TO OUR SHIP.

305
00:17:44,355 --> 00:17:47,901
THERE'S A HALF-CENTIMETER
OF XYLATHORIC ACID ON THAT DECK.

306
00:17:47,942 --> 00:17:49,402
I WOULDN'T RECOMMEND IT,

307
00:17:49,443 --> 00:17:51,946
NOT IF YOU VALUE
THOSE PRETTY FEET OF YOURS.

308
00:17:51,988 --> 00:17:55,825
DO YOU HAVE SOMEWHERE
WE CAN PUT HIM UNTIL WE LEAVE?

309
00:17:55,867 --> 00:17:58,995
DOES THIS LOOK
LIKE A PRISON TO YOU?

310
00:18:09,088 --> 00:18:12,132
ANY ONE OF THESE PEOPLE
COULD BE WORKING WITH HIM.

311
00:18:12,174 --> 00:18:15,595
T'POL: THE MINISTRY OF SECURITY
WAS VERY CLEAR ABOUT THAT.

312
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:17,555
HE WORKS ALONE.

313
00:18:17,597 --> 00:18:20,558
I HAVEN'T ALWAYS.

314
00:18:21,267 --> 00:18:24,144
[ PANTING ]

315
00:18:32,528 --> 00:18:34,072
YOU'RE HUMAN.

316
00:18:36,407 --> 00:18:38,618
AND YOU AS WELL.

317
00:18:40,411 --> 00:18:45,374
THEY WANTED
TO REHABILITATE ME...

318
00:18:45,416 --> 00:18:48,544
BRING ME HOME...

319
00:18:48,586 --> 00:18:52,757
FLATTEN MY FOREHEAD
AND RE-POINT MY EARS.

320
00:18:52,799 --> 00:18:55,843
THEY WANTED TO TEACH ME
TO FORGET THE LIFE

321
00:18:55,885 --> 00:18:59,346
THEY HAD TAUGHT ME
SO CAREFULLY HOW TO LIVE.

322
00:18:59,388 --> 00:19:03,684
THEY ASSUMED
I HAD BECOME CORRUPT

323
00:19:03,726 --> 00:19:06,353
AND THAT,
LEFT TO MY OWN DEVICES,

324
00:19:06,395 --> 00:19:09,482
I WOULD REMAIN CORRUPT.

325
00:19:11,067 --> 00:19:14,654
THREE YEARS IN A VULCAN CLINIC.

326
00:19:14,695 --> 00:19:17,115
REHABILITATION.

327
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:22,036
[ CHUCKLES ]
CAN YOU BLAME ME FOR RUNNING?

328
00:19:22,078 --> 00:19:23,663
[ SIGHS ]

329
00:19:23,704 --> 00:19:26,124
I'M NOT A THIEF.

330
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:30,670
I'M NOT A SMUGGLER.
I NEVER WAS.

331
00:19:30,711 --> 00:19:32,839
I WORKED WITH SMUGGLERS.

332
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:35,883
I WORKED VERY CLOSE WITH THEM
FOR A LONG TIME.

333
00:19:35,925 --> 00:19:38,928
IT'S WHAT I HAD BEEN TRAINED
TO DO.

334
00:19:38,970 --> 00:19:43,057
DO YOU KNOW HOW I'VE SURVIVED
THE LAST 20 YEARS,

335
00:19:43,099 --> 00:19:44,851
HOW I'VE FED MY FAMILY?

336
00:19:44,892 --> 00:19:48,646
I HAUL
SPENT WARP-INJECTOR CASINGS --

337
00:19:48,688 --> 00:19:51,065
NOT A VERY POPULAR OCCUPATION,

338
00:19:51,107 --> 00:19:54,694
BUT A NECESSARY ONE.

339
00:19:54,735 --> 00:19:56,863
A DOCTOR ON ANDORIA SAYS

340
00:19:56,904 --> 00:20:00,366
THAT MY HEMOLYTIC-CELL COUNT
IS OVER 3,000.

341
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:05,830
YOU DON'T FIND TOO MANY OLD MEN
HAULING SPENT INJECTOR CASINGS.

342
00:20:07,414 --> 00:20:12,586
UH, IN MY LEFT FRONT POCKET,
IF YOU DON'T MIND.

343
00:20:12,628 --> 00:20:15,048
I WOULDN'T. IT MAY BE A WEAPON.

344
00:20:15,089 --> 00:20:18,718
IT'S A HOLOGRAM OF MY FAMILY.

345
00:20:18,759 --> 00:20:20,302
IT WON'T HURT YOU.

346
00:20:40,447 --> 00:20:42,700
THE INJECTOR CASINGS

347
00:20:42,742 --> 00:20:44,785
ARE GOING TO TAKE ME AWAY
FROM THEM SOON ENOUGH.

348
00:20:44,827 --> 00:20:47,038
I DON'T WANT TO DIE
IN A VULCAN PRISON.

349
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:48,748
THE INFORMATION
THAT I WAS GIVEN

350
00:20:48,789 --> 00:20:50,833
SAYS THAT YOU BUY
HIGH-GRADE BIO-TOXINS

351
00:20:50,875 --> 00:20:53,419
AND SELL THEM TO ANYONE
WHO WILL MEET YOUR PRICE.

352
00:20:53,460 --> 00:20:55,963
IF ALL OF THE MINISTRY'S REPORTS
ABOUT ME WERE TRUE,

353
00:20:56,005 --> 00:20:59,759
I COULD EASILY SHAPE-SHIFT AND
SLIP OUT OF THESE RESTRAINTS,

354
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:03,470
OR SPROUT WINGS
AND FLY TO MY SHIP.

355
00:21:03,512 --> 00:21:05,139
ARCHER: WHY SHOULD SHE
BELIEVE A FUGITIVE

356
00:21:05,181 --> 00:21:06,557
AND NOT HER OWN GOVERNMENT?

357
00:21:06,599 --> 00:21:10,144
BECAUSE HER GOVERNMENT
SENT 109 AGENTS

358
00:21:10,186 --> 00:21:12,230
TO AGARON 30 YEARS AGO,

359
00:21:12,271 --> 00:21:15,524
AND THEY WANT
ALL 109 ACCOUNTED FOR,

360
00:21:15,566 --> 00:21:18,360
RIGHT OR WRONG,
DEAD OR ALIVE.

361
00:21:18,402 --> 00:21:20,029
IF YOU'RE INNOCENT,

362
00:21:20,071 --> 00:21:21,948
I'M SURE YOU'LL BE GIVEN
A CHANCE TO DEFEND YOURSELF.

363
00:21:21,989 --> 00:21:23,449
WELL, I'M GUILTY.

364
00:21:23,490 --> 00:21:26,953
I'M GUILTY OF NOT RETURNING
WHEN I WAS TOLD TO.

365
00:21:26,994 --> 00:21:30,248
I'M INNOCENT
OF SELLING BIO-TOXINS,

366
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:32,959
BUT I'M GUILTY
OF BEING A FUGITIVE.

367
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:35,711
BUT I DON'T DESERVE
TO GO TO PRISON,

368
00:21:35,753 --> 00:21:37,421
AND I DON'T DESERVE TO BE SHOT.

369
00:21:37,463 --> 00:21:39,506
WE'RE HERE TO TAKE YOU
TO VULCAN.

370
00:21:39,548 --> 00:21:41,550
NO ONE'S GOING TO SHOOT YOU.

371
00:21:41,592 --> 00:21:44,303
WHAT ABOUT HER?

372
00:21:45,596 --> 00:21:48,141
[ PANTING ]

373
00:21:50,559 --> 00:21:52,895
[ SCREAMING ]

374
00:21:52,937 --> 00:21:55,148
YOU'RE A LIAR.

375
00:21:57,524 --> 00:21:59,652
T'POL!

376
00:22:05,616 --> 00:22:07,660
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

377
00:22:07,701 --> 00:22:09,162
T'POL?

378
00:22:09,203 --> 00:22:11,580
HE'S NOT TELLING THE TRUTH.

379
00:22:18,838 --> 00:22:20,631
WHERE THE HELL
ARE YOU GOING?

380
00:22:20,673 --> 00:22:22,424
T'POL!

381
00:22:22,466 --> 00:22:26,220
HE SAYS HE HAS A SHIP
FULL OF INJECTOR CASINGS.

382
00:22:26,262 --> 00:22:28,430
ARCHER: BUT THE PLATFORM'S
COVERED WITH ACID.

383
00:23:14,685 --> 00:23:16,812
[ PANTING ]

384
00:23:16,854 --> 00:23:18,396
[ GRUNTS ]

385
00:23:18,438 --> 00:23:20,358
JOSSEN!

386
00:23:20,398 --> 00:23:22,526
[ SCREAMING ]

387
00:23:50,930 --> 00:23:52,306
YOU'RE SURE?

388
00:23:52,348 --> 00:23:55,184
THERE'S NO RECORD OF THEM
EVER HAVING SPOKEN,

389
00:23:55,226 --> 00:23:56,685
BUT I CAN'T BE CERTAIN.

390
00:23:56,727 --> 00:23:58,604
HAS HE EVER BEEN TO EARTH?

391
00:23:58,645 --> 00:24:01,774
IF HE HAS, THE VULCAN DATABASE
DOESN'T MENTION IT.

392
00:24:01,815 --> 00:24:03,650
WELL, I HOPE THEY HAVEN'T PUT

393
00:24:03,692 --> 00:24:06,112
STARFLEET YEARBOOK PHOTOS
INTO THAT DATABASE.

394
00:24:06,153 --> 00:24:09,698
OH, LET'S GET THIS OVER WITH.

395
00:24:18,707 --> 00:24:24,004
CAPTAIN TAVEK, IS THERE
SOMETHING I CAN DO FOR YOU?

396
00:24:24,046 --> 00:24:25,672
TAVEK:<i> CAPTAIN ARCHER?</i>

397
00:24:25,714 --> 00:24:27,174
YES?

398
00:24:29,218 --> 00:24:32,012
IS...THERE A PROBLEM?

399
00:24:32,054 --> 00:24:35,724
<i>YOU SEEM VERY YOUNG</i>
<i>FOR A STARFLEET CAPTAIN.</i>

400
00:24:35,766 --> 00:24:38,436
HEALTHY LIVING.

401
00:24:38,476 --> 00:24:42,022
YOU HAVE A MESSAGE
FROM ADMIRAL FORREST?

402
00:24:42,064 --> 00:24:43,649
<i>I'M NOT CERTAIN</i>
<i>WHAT THIS MEANS,</i>

403
00:24:43,690 --> 00:24:47,069
<i>BUT THE ADMIRAL ASKED ME</i>
<i>TO INFORM YOU THAT...</i>

404
00:24:47,111 --> 00:24:51,698
<i>CAL BEAT STANFORD,</i>
<i>SEVEN TO THREE.</i>

405
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:53,700
I'LL BE SURE TO TELL HIM.

406
00:24:53,742 --> 00:24:54,910
<i>TELL WHO?</i>

407
00:24:54,952 --> 00:24:58,914
UM, I'M AFRAID
IT'S CONFIDENTIAL.

408
00:24:58,956 --> 00:25:01,000
THANK YOU
FOR RELAYING THE MESSAGE.

409
00:25:01,041 --> 00:25:02,793
ARCHER OUT.

410
00:25:07,089 --> 00:25:09,300
[ SIGHS ]

411
00:25:20,019 --> 00:25:21,854
THAT WASN'T TOO SMART.

412
00:25:21,895 --> 00:25:23,939
YOU COULD HAVE BEEN HURT.

413
00:25:23,981 --> 00:25:27,693
WHAT DID YOU FIND?

414
00:25:27,734 --> 00:25:30,196
T'POL:
SPENT INJECTOR CASINGS.

415
00:25:31,738 --> 00:25:34,992
YOU'LL HAVE TO GO THROUGH DECON
WHEN WE GET BACK.

416
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:41,790
I WANT TO SPEAK TO MENOS ALONE.

417
00:25:41,832 --> 00:25:44,210
WOULD YOU ALLOW ME TO DO THAT?

418
00:25:46,462 --> 00:25:48,422
ARCHER: COME ON, TRAVIS.

419
00:25:48,464 --> 00:25:51,758
LET'S SEE IF WE CAN FIND
SOMETHING TO EAT.

420
00:26:08,859 --> 00:26:10,444
[ GRUNTS ]

421
00:26:17,868 --> 00:26:20,454
[ SIGHS ]

422
00:26:20,496 --> 00:26:21,955
WHO IS JOSSEN?

423
00:26:21,997 --> 00:26:26,210
YOU DIDN'T FIND WHAT YOU
WERE LOOKING FOR, DID YOU?

424
00:26:26,252 --> 00:26:28,337
WHO IS JOSSEN?

425
00:26:28,379 --> 00:26:31,631
IF THIS IS YOUR IDEA OF HUMOR...

426
00:26:33,092 --> 00:26:35,844
TELL ME WHO HE IS.

427
00:26:35,886 --> 00:26:39,390
JOSSEN WAS NO DIFFERENT THAN ME.

428
00:26:41,267 --> 00:26:44,728
HE DIDN'T WANT
TO BE REHABILITATED, EITHER.

429
00:26:46,897 --> 00:26:47,940
[ GRUNTS ]

430
00:26:50,901 --> 00:26:52,819
WHERE DID I MEET HIM?

431
00:26:52,861 --> 00:26:54,905
MEET HIM?

432
00:26:54,947 --> 00:26:57,283
ON RISA.

433
00:26:57,324 --> 00:27:00,494
JOSSEN AND I WERE ON RISA
IN THE TROPICAL ZONE.

434
00:27:00,536 --> 00:27:02,871
WE WERE INNOCENT
OF THE CRIMES

435
00:27:02,913 --> 00:27:04,248
THE MINISTRY HAD ACCUSED US OF,

436
00:27:04,290 --> 00:27:06,584
BUT WE WERE RUNNING
ALL THE SAME.

437
00:27:09,878 --> 00:27:14,091
WHY DO YOU WANT ME TO TELL YOU
THINGS YOU ALREADY KNOW?

438
00:27:14,133 --> 00:27:17,010
YOU'RE TELLING ME LIES.

439
00:27:17,052 --> 00:27:18,429
NO. THE TRUTH.

440
00:27:18,471 --> 00:27:23,725
I FOLLOWED YOU TO RISA,
NO ONE ELSE.

441
00:27:23,767 --> 00:27:27,104
I BRIBED THE TELLARITE TRANSPORT
CAPTAIN WHO BROUGHT YOU THERE.

442
00:27:27,146 --> 00:27:29,440
HE TOLD ME EXACTLY
WHERE TO FIND YOU.

443
00:27:29,482 --> 00:27:32,151
I WASN'T LOOKING
FOR ANYONE ELSE.

444
00:27:32,192 --> 00:27:34,820
THEN WHY ARE YOU
ASKING ME ABOUT JOSSEN?

445
00:27:34,861 --> 00:27:37,739
HE NEVER HURT ANYONE.

446
00:27:37,781 --> 00:27:41,785
HE DIDN'T DESERVE TO BE
HUNTED DOWN LIKE AN ANIMAL.

447
00:27:43,621 --> 00:27:44,830
[ WEAPON FIRES ]

448
00:27:44,871 --> 00:27:47,374
I KILLED HIM.

449
00:27:47,416 --> 00:27:51,629
YES. AND HE DIDN'T
DESERVE TO BE KILLED.

450
00:27:51,669 --> 00:27:55,007
HE WAS AN INNOCENT MAN,
JUST LIKE I AM.

451
00:27:59,677 --> 00:28:01,263
[ GROANS ]

452
00:28:02,431 --> 00:28:04,975
YOU REALLY DON'T REMEMBER.

453
00:28:05,017 --> 00:28:06,560
HOW IS THAT POSSIBLE?

454
00:28:06,602 --> 00:28:10,314
WHY DID YOU KILL HIM?
HE NEVER WOULD HAVE HURT YOU.

455
00:28:10,356 --> 00:28:12,191
STOP TALKING.

456
00:28:12,232 --> 00:28:13,733
YOU'RE A VULCAN.

457
00:28:13,775 --> 00:28:16,320
YOU'RE TRAINED TO REPRESS
THE EMOTION OF KILLING,

458
00:28:16,362 --> 00:28:18,947
NOT THE MEMORY OF THE ACT.

459
00:28:18,989 --> 00:28:19,948
AAH!

460
00:28:19,990 --> 00:28:21,783
I SAID STOP TALKING!

461
00:28:21,825 --> 00:28:24,911
LOOK WHAT IT'S DONE TO YOU --
TAKING AN INNOCENT LIFE.

462
00:28:24,953 --> 00:28:27,789
BRINGING ME BACK TO VULCAN
WILL BE NO DIFFERENT.

463
00:28:27,831 --> 00:28:29,958
YOU'LL BE DESTROYING
ANOTHER LIFE.

464
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:31,627
HOW WILL THAT AFFECT YOU?

465
00:28:31,669 --> 00:28:35,255
WILL YOU CONVENIENTLY FORGET
WHAT YOU'RE ABOUT TO DO TO ME?

466
00:28:38,300 --> 00:28:41,053
WHERE'S MENOS?

467
00:28:44,973 --> 00:28:47,351
ARCHER: GET BACK OVER THERE.
TRAVIS: AYE, SIR.

468
00:29:02,824 --> 00:29:04,660
WHAT HAPPENED?

469
00:29:07,663 --> 00:29:09,789
THERE WERE SEVEN.

470
00:29:09,831 --> 00:29:11,500
SEVEN WHAT?

471
00:29:11,542 --> 00:29:16,255
I WAS SENT TO BRING BACK
SEVEN FUGITIVES, NOT SIX.

472
00:29:16,296 --> 00:29:18,006
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

473
00:29:19,966 --> 00:29:25,431
MENOS HAD A PARTNER
OR A FRIEND -- I'M NOT SURE.

474
00:29:28,975 --> 00:29:30,810
HIS NAME WAS JOSSEN.

475
00:29:30,852 --> 00:29:35,148
I FOLLOWED THEM BOTH TO RISA,
NOT JUST MENOS.

476
00:29:35,190 --> 00:29:40,446
THE DAY I TOLD YOU I SAW MENOS
AND LOST HIM,

477
00:29:40,487 --> 00:29:42,989
I SAW JOSSEN AS WELL.

478
00:29:43,031 --> 00:29:46,826
THEY TRIED TO ESCAPE.
JOSSEN FELL TO THE GROUND.

479
00:29:49,288 --> 00:29:52,750
HE BEGAN TO REACH
FOR HIS WEAPON.

480
00:29:54,126 --> 00:29:55,586
BUT YOU FIRED FIRST?

481
00:29:55,628 --> 00:30:01,508
I HAD FORGOTTEN ALL OF IT
UNTIL TODAY.

482
00:30:01,550 --> 00:30:03,135
HOW?

483
00:30:03,176 --> 00:30:06,555
HAVE YOU HEARD OF THE FULLARA?

484
00:30:06,597 --> 00:30:08,265
NO.

485
00:30:08,307 --> 00:30:10,934
IT'S AN OBSOLETE VULCAN RITUAL

486
00:30:10,976 --> 00:30:14,271
WHERE THE MEMORY OF AN EVENT
IS REPRESSED

487
00:30:14,313 --> 00:30:18,567
ALONG WITH THE EMOTIONS
ASSOCIATED WITH IT.

488
00:30:18,609 --> 00:30:21,403
AND YOU HAD THIS...

489
00:30:21,445 --> 00:30:22,655
FULLARA.

490
00:30:22,696 --> 00:30:25,616
THIS FULLARA RITUAL
PERFORMED?

491
00:30:25,658 --> 00:30:30,663
T'POL: WHEN I RETURNED TO
VULCAN, I WAS UNSETTLED.

492
00:30:30,704 --> 00:30:33,915
I RESIGNED MY POSITION
WITH THE MINISTRY

493
00:30:33,957 --> 00:30:38,462
AND SOUGHT GUIDANCE
AT THE SANCTUARY OF P'JEM.

494
00:30:38,504 --> 00:30:40,714
FOR MONTHS, ONE OF THE ELDERS
WORKED WITH ME

495
00:30:40,756 --> 00:30:43,300
TO CONTROL THE GUILT,

496
00:30:43,342 --> 00:30:50,349
TO RESTRAIN THE DESPAIR
OF HAVING TAKEN A LIFE,

497
00:30:50,390 --> 00:30:52,726
BUT THE FEELINGS REMAINED.

498
00:30:52,768 --> 00:30:58,106
WHY WOULD YOU FEEL GUILTY
IF THIS JOSSEN

499
00:30:58,148 --> 00:31:00,192
WAS ABOUT TO FIRE AT YOU?

500
00:31:03,987 --> 00:31:07,907
I SUPPOSE I WAS NEVER CERTAIN
WHAT HIS INTENTIONS WERE.

501
00:31:07,949 --> 00:31:12,371
THE ELDER HAD NO CHOICE
BUT TO PERFORM THE RITUAL.

502
00:31:12,412 --> 00:31:15,040
WHEN I LEFT THE SANCTUARY,

503
00:31:15,081 --> 00:31:18,377
I DIDN'T REMEMBER ANYTHING
ABOUT JOSSEN OR THE FULLARA.

504
00:31:18,418 --> 00:31:20,086
WHEN DID IT START COMING BACK?

505
00:31:20,128 --> 00:31:24,174
WHEN THE FIRST CALL CAME IN
ABOUT THIS NEW MISSION.

506
00:31:24,216 --> 00:31:27,010
MAYBE THAT'S WHY
I WANTED YOU WITH ME.

507
00:31:27,052 --> 00:31:30,138
WHAT IF JOSSEN
WASN'T A SMUGGLER?

508
00:31:30,180 --> 00:31:31,515
WHAT IF HE WAS INNOCENT?

509
00:31:31,557 --> 00:31:32,932
THEN IT WOULDN'T HAVE MATTERED

510
00:31:32,974 --> 00:31:35,143
WHETHER HE INTENDED TO USE
THAT WEAPON OR NOT.

511
00:31:35,185 --> 00:31:37,937
THAT DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

512
00:31:37,979 --> 00:31:39,773
WHAT'S MENOS BEEN TELLING YOU?

513
00:31:39,815 --> 00:31:44,403
MENOS' SHIP WAS FILLED WITH
INJECTOR CASINGS, NOTHING ELSE.

514
00:31:44,444 --> 00:31:47,072
HE HAS A FAMILY.

515
00:31:47,113 --> 00:31:48,782
OUR SCANS SHOULD BE ABLE
TO CONFIRM IF HE'S DYING

516
00:31:48,824 --> 00:31:50,617
OF RADIATION POISONING.

517
00:31:50,659 --> 00:31:52,160
WHAT'S HE BEEN TELLING YOU?

518
00:31:52,202 --> 00:31:54,246
[ CRASH, INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

519
00:32:01,795 --> 00:32:04,798
HE KICKED OVER THE TABLE!

520
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:07,133
AND YOU CLAIM YOU'RE
A PEACEFUL MAN.

521
00:32:07,175 --> 00:32:09,386
IRONIC, ISN'T IT?

522
00:32:09,428 --> 00:32:11,388
BURNING TO DEATH
ON A FROZEN MOON?

523
00:32:11,430 --> 00:32:13,432
BUT I'D RATHER DIE HERE
THAN BE BROUGHT BACK

524
00:32:13,473 --> 00:32:16,393
AND PUNISHED FOR CRIMES
I NEVER COMMITTED.

525
00:32:16,435 --> 00:32:18,687
T'POL!

526
00:32:23,233 --> 00:32:24,735
REFASTEN THEM.

527
00:32:26,862 --> 00:32:28,280
OH!

528
00:32:33,243 --> 00:32:35,746
T'POL: WHERE'S MENOS?
ARCHER: TRAVIS!

529
00:32:40,208 --> 00:32:41,585
COME ON.

530
00:32:44,212 --> 00:32:45,839
WHERE'S HIS SHIP?

531
00:32:45,881 --> 00:32:48,133
YOUR MISSION IS
TO RETURN HIM TO VULCAN,

532
00:32:48,174 --> 00:32:50,803
NOT DETERMINE
WHETHER HE'S GUILTY OR INNOCENT.

533
00:32:50,844 --> 00:32:52,763
WHERE'S HIS SHIP?

534
00:33:16,244 --> 00:33:18,330
HE'S NOT ABOARD.

535
00:33:22,167 --> 00:33:24,043
LET'S BE SURE.

536
00:33:36,890 --> 00:33:39,935
WE'LL ALL NEED TO GO
THROUGH DECON NOW.

537
00:33:51,279 --> 00:33:53,281
HE'S NOT HERE.

538
00:33:53,323 --> 00:33:55,659
WAS THAT THE ONLY WAY IN?

539
00:33:55,701 --> 00:33:57,995
GO BACK TO THE COCKPIT, TRAVIS.

540
00:33:58,036 --> 00:33:59,746
AYE, SIR.

541
00:33:59,788 --> 00:34:01,832
ARCHER: GET LIFE SUPPORT
FIRED UP IF YOU CAN.
IT'S PRETTY COLD.

542
00:34:08,296 --> 00:34:11,299
HE SHOULD'VE GOTTEN HERE
BEFORE US.

543
00:34:11,341 --> 00:34:13,510
THIS SHIP SHOULDN'T BE HERE.

544
00:34:13,552 --> 00:34:16,513
T'POL: WHY RISK USING
HIS OWN VESSEL?

545
00:34:16,555 --> 00:34:18,223
HE'D KNOW WE'D FOLLOW HIM.

546
00:34:18,264 --> 00:34:22,143
SO HE COULD'VE LEFT WITH
ANY ONE OF THOSE OTHER SHIPS.

547
00:34:22,185 --> 00:34:24,563
ANY ONE OF THEM.

548
00:34:24,604 --> 00:34:26,732
YOU SEEM OKAY WITH THAT.

549
00:34:27,941 --> 00:34:30,235
WHEN WE RETURN TO<i> ENTERPRISE,</i>

550
00:34:30,276 --> 00:34:33,739
I'LL INFORM THE VULCAN SHIP
THAT MENOS ESCAPED.

551
00:34:33,780 --> 00:34:35,281
IF THE HIGH COMMAND WISHES,

552
00:34:35,323 --> 00:34:37,951
THEY CAN QUESTION AS MANY
OF THE VESSELS THAT LEFT HERE

553
00:34:37,993 --> 00:34:39,619
AS THEY CAN FIND.

554
00:34:39,661 --> 00:34:42,288
YOU'RE GIVING UP A LOT EASIER
THAN I WOULD'VE GUESSED.

555
00:34:42,330 --> 00:34:43,707
HE'S OBVIOUSLY GONE.

556
00:34:43,749 --> 00:34:45,584
WE DON'T KNOW THAT.

557
00:34:49,755 --> 00:34:51,339
HE GOT TO YOU, DIDN'T HE?

558
00:34:51,381 --> 00:34:54,342
YOU'RE BEGINNING
TO DOUBT YOURSELF.

559
00:34:54,384 --> 00:34:55,677
HE FIGURED IF HE COULD GET YOU

560
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:58,179
TO QUESTION
WHAT YOU DID 17 YEARS AGO,

561
00:34:58,221 --> 00:35:00,306
YOU'D BEGIN TO QUESTION
WHAT YOU'RE DOING RIGHT NOW.

562
00:35:00,348 --> 00:35:02,935
I MAY HAVE KILLED
AN INNOCENT MAN 17 YEARS AGO.

563
00:35:02,976 --> 00:35:04,686
DID JOSSEN REACH
FOR HIS WEAPON OR NOT?

564
00:35:04,728 --> 00:35:06,438
T'POL: I DON'T KNOW.
ARCHER: IS THAT
WHAT YOU REMEMBER

565
00:35:06,479 --> 00:35:07,689
OR WHAT MENOS WANTS YOU
TO REMEMBER?

566
00:35:07,731 --> 00:35:08,899
WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?

567
00:35:08,941 --> 00:35:10,442
THERE'S A BIG
DIFFERENCE.

568
00:35:10,483 --> 00:35:11,860
HE'S PLAYING ON YOUR GUILT.
DON'T YOU SEE THAT?

569
00:35:11,902 --> 00:35:15,363
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.
I WENT TO P'JEM.

570
00:35:15,405 --> 00:35:16,656
THEY PERFORMED THE RITUAL --

571
00:35:16,698 --> 00:35:18,241
DON'T GIVE ME THAT!

572
00:35:18,283 --> 00:35:20,410
YOUR EMOTIONAL IMMUNE SYSTEM
STARTED TO COLLAPSE AGAIN

573
00:35:20,452 --> 00:35:23,413
THE MINUTE YOU REMEMBERED
WHAT HAPPENED THAT DAY ON RISA.

574
00:35:23,455 --> 00:35:25,916
TRAVIS: CAPTAIN.
ARCHER: WHAT IS IT, TRAVIS?

575
00:35:25,958 --> 00:35:27,709
THERE'S SOMETHING FUNNY
UP HERE, SIR.

576
00:35:27,751 --> 00:35:29,461
YOU THINK YOU COULD TAKE A LOOK?

577
00:35:34,674 --> 00:35:35,926
ARCHER: WHAT'S UP?

578
00:35:35,968 --> 00:35:37,677
AFTER I GOT THE BOARD RUNNING,

579
00:35:37,719 --> 00:35:39,805
I BROUGHT LIFE SUPPORT UP
TO LEVEL THREE.

580
00:35:39,846 --> 00:35:41,640
AS SOON AS I GOT
MORE LIGHT IN HERE,

581
00:35:41,681 --> 00:35:44,101
I NOTICED SOME CONDENSATION
ON THIS SUB-PANEL.

582
00:35:44,142 --> 00:35:45,560
ARCHER: THERE'S A HELL OF
A LOT OF ENERGY FLOWING

583
00:35:45,602 --> 00:35:47,020
THROUGH THOSE CIRCUITS.

584
00:35:47,062 --> 00:35:48,521
ANY IDEA WHAT THEY ARE?

585
00:35:48,563 --> 00:35:51,483
OUR SCANNER SHOWED
EVERYTHING POWERED DOWN.

586
00:35:51,524 --> 00:35:56,154
WELL, OBVIOUSLY,
SOMETHING'S POWERED UP.

587
00:35:56,195 --> 00:35:59,074
THERE'S ONE WAY TO
FIND OUT WHAT IT IS.

588
00:36:04,370 --> 00:36:07,040
I'M A VERY PATIENT MAN, T'POL.

589
00:36:07,082 --> 00:36:09,334
I WAS SIMPLY WAITING
FOR YOU TO LEAVE,

590
00:36:09,375 --> 00:36:13,630
BUT YOUR CAPTAIN'S CURIOSITY
HAS PUT AN END TO THAT.

591
00:36:13,672 --> 00:36:16,341
WOULD YOU PLEASE
LOWER YOUR WEAPON?

592
00:36:20,971 --> 00:36:23,807
ARCHER: THERE'S SOME KIND
OF ENERGY FIELD RUNNING...

593
00:36:23,849 --> 00:36:27,894
I DON'T WANT TO HARM T'POL,
CAPTAIN, BUT I WILL.

594
00:36:27,936 --> 00:36:31,106
THOSE ARE VIOLENT WORDS
FOR A PEACEFUL MAN.

595
00:36:31,148 --> 00:36:35,234
AT THE MOMENT, I'M A MAN
WHO NEEDS TO SURVIVE.

596
00:36:36,778 --> 00:36:39,823
THERE'S A LOCKER
RIGHT NEXT TO YOU.

597
00:36:39,865 --> 00:36:43,076
I WANT YOU TO BOTH
PUT YOUR WEAPONS DOWN

598
00:36:43,118 --> 00:36:44,452
AND THEN WALK INTO IT.

599
00:36:44,494 --> 00:36:45,787
YOU WON'T BE HURT.

600
00:36:45,829 --> 00:36:47,539
WHAT ABOUT HER?

601
00:36:47,580 --> 00:36:51,043
MENOS: T'POL IS MY GUARANTEE
THAT THE TWO OF YOU WILL WALK

602
00:36:51,084 --> 00:36:54,880
QUICKLY AND QUIETLY
INTO THE LOCKER.

603
00:36:54,921 --> 00:36:56,548
PLEASE.

604
00:37:19,946 --> 00:37:23,241
THE LOCKING CODE IS 1661.

605
00:37:23,282 --> 00:37:27,037
THERE'S A VERY SPECIFIC TONE
WHEN IT'S ENTERED PROPERLY.

606
00:37:29,539 --> 00:37:30,832
[ GRUNTS ]

607
00:37:34,460 --> 00:37:36,838
ARCHER: YOU OKAY?
T'POL: YES.

608
00:37:42,260 --> 00:37:44,804
WE DON'T DO QUICKLY AND QUIETLY
VERY WELL,

609
00:37:44,846 --> 00:37:46,472
BUT WE ARE GOOD
AT ARITHMETIC.

610
00:37:46,514 --> 00:37:50,602
SEEMS THERE ARE THREE OF US
AND ONLY ONE OF YOU.

611
00:37:55,190 --> 00:37:57,609
STOP! PLEASE!

612
00:38:03,531 --> 00:38:04,783
I DON'T TRUST THIS GUY, TRAVIS.

613
00:38:04,824 --> 00:38:06,159
FIND SOMETHING TO
TIE HIM UP WITH.

614
00:38:06,201 --> 00:38:07,827
AYE, SIR.

615
00:38:09,579 --> 00:38:10,997
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

616
00:38:13,583 --> 00:38:15,252
GET UP!

617
00:38:24,594 --> 00:38:25,845
STOP!

618
00:38:29,474 --> 00:38:31,851
YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO SHOOT ME, T'POL.

619
00:38:31,893 --> 00:38:34,062
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO KILL
ANOTHER INNOCENT MAN.

620
00:38:34,104 --> 00:38:38,483
MENOS: THIS IS NONE
OF YOUR CONCERN, CAPTAIN.

621
00:38:38,524 --> 00:38:41,569
YOU KNOW NOTHING
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED ON RISA.

622
00:38:48,243 --> 00:38:50,578
CAPTAIN?

623
00:38:52,872 --> 00:38:56,584
WHY DID YOU WANT ME HERE?

624
00:38:56,626 --> 00:38:58,586
BECAUSE I TRUST YOU.

625
00:38:58,628 --> 00:39:00,546
THEN TRUST ME.

626
00:39:00,588 --> 00:39:04,968
YOU WERE SENT TO APPREHEND HIM,
NOT TO JUDGE HIM.

627
00:39:08,680 --> 00:39:11,183
[ GRUNTS ]

628
00:39:18,148 --> 00:39:20,692
HE'S NOT GONNA GET
OUT OF THAT TOO QUICKLY.

629
00:39:20,733 --> 00:39:22,568
TRAVIS: I THINK I KNOW
WHY HE WAS SO NERVOUS

630
00:39:22,610 --> 00:39:24,988
ABOUT US FIRING AT HIM
WHILE HE WAS OVER HERE.

631
00:39:25,030 --> 00:39:26,656
LOOK AT THIS.

632
00:39:32,287 --> 00:39:33,621
BIO-TOXINS.

633
00:39:33,663 --> 00:39:37,542
IF ONE OF OUR WEAPONS
HAD STRUCK THIS...

634
00:39:39,211 --> 00:39:42,922
I GUESS HE WAS HAULING MORE THAN
INJECTOR CASINGS, AFTER ALL.

635
00:39:45,300 --> 00:39:47,344
I GUESS HE WAS.

636
00:39:51,681 --> 00:39:55,060
ARCHER: CAPTAIN'S STARLOG,
SUPPLEMENTAL.

637
00:39:55,101 --> 00:39:57,062
THE VULCAN SHIP<i> NYRAN</i>
<i>WAS WAITING</i>

638
00:39:57,103 --> 00:39:58,688
AT THE PREARRANGED COORDINATES.

639
00:39:58,730 --> 00:40:01,482
AFTER TRANSFERRING MENOS
TO THEIR CUSTODY,

640
00:40:01,524 --> 00:40:03,693
WE'VE RETURNED TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

641
00:40:04,610 --> 00:40:06,154
WHAT'S YOUR STATUS, TRIP?

642
00:40:06,196 --> 00:40:08,823
Trip: Everything's ready to go,
Captain. Welcome back.

643
00:40:08,865 --> 00:40:11,243
THANKS.
WE'LL BE GOING TO WARP 3.

644
00:40:11,284 --> 00:40:12,451
Trip: You got it.

645
00:40:12,493 --> 00:40:14,371
UM...

646
00:40:14,412 --> 00:40:15,997
NOW THAT YOUR SECRET MISSION
IS OVER,

647
00:40:16,039 --> 00:40:17,832
YOU THINK YOU COULD GIVE
YOUR CHIEF ENGINEER

648
00:40:17,874 --> 00:40:21,044
A LITTLE HINT
ABOUT WHAT YOU WERE UP TO?

649
00:40:21,086 --> 00:40:25,131
DID I SAY WARP 3?
I MEANT WARP 4, COMMANDER.

650
00:40:26,341 --> 00:40:28,009
NOT EVEN A HINT?

651
00:40:30,636 --> 00:40:33,390
WARP 4. AYE, CAPTAIN.

652
00:40:35,350 --> 00:40:36,559
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

653
00:40:36,601 --> 00:40:37,769
COME IN.

654
00:40:40,188 --> 00:40:41,647
SUBCOMMANDER.

655
00:40:41,689 --> 00:40:45,318
AM I ABOUT TO GET ANOTHER CALL
FROM ADMIRAL FORREST?

656
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:47,404
NO, SIR.

657
00:40:49,364 --> 00:40:50,698
SORRY.

658
00:40:53,285 --> 00:40:56,955
DEALING WITH THESE MEMORIES --

659
00:40:56,996 --> 00:41:02,001
IT'S NOT GOING TO BE
EASY FOR YOU, IS IT?

660
00:41:02,043 --> 00:41:05,130
NO, IT'S NOT.

661
00:41:05,171 --> 00:41:07,299
IF YOU FEEL YOU NEED
A LEAVE OF ABSENCE --

662
00:41:07,340 --> 00:41:09,968
THAT WON'T BE NECESSARY.

663
00:41:10,009 --> 00:41:12,345
I WAS MUCH YOUNGER THEN.

664
00:41:12,387 --> 00:41:15,681
YOU'VE ALSO SPENT A LOT OF TIME
AROUND HUMANS LATELY.

665
00:41:15,723 --> 00:41:19,144
YOU DO HAVE A WAY OF PUTTING
QUESTIONABLE ACTIONS BEHIND YOU.

666
00:41:19,185 --> 00:41:23,273
WHEN YOU DON'T HAVE THE ABILITY
TO REPRESS EMOTIONS,

667
00:41:23,315 --> 00:41:27,068
YOU LEARN TO DEAL WITH THEM
AND MOVE ON.

668
00:41:29,862 --> 00:41:32,949
WAS THERE SOMETHING ELSE?

669
00:41:32,991 --> 00:41:36,702
IF YOU EVER NEED
SOMEONE YOU CAN TRUST...

670
00:41:36,744 --> 00:41:39,122
I WON'T FORGET.
